# Built example/test binaries dropped at repo root.
# `go build ./examples/foo/bar/baz` writes a binary named "baz" at $PWD.
# When $PWD is the repo root, that binary clutters the tree. Each name
# below corresponds to an examples/ or tests/edge_cases/ subdirectory.
# Add an entry here if a new example starts producing root-level cruft;
# better, run examples via `go run ./examples/...` (no binary emitted)
# or `go build -o /tmp/foo ./examples/...`.
/arbitrary_keys
/balances
/cancel
/callback
/failed_retry
/file
/grant-token
/hello-world
/http_callback
/http_channel
